The paper deals with the problem of extracting features from compressive measurements, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.IT). The paper also proposes a deep learning framework, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments conducted in the paper involve imaging and signal processing, which are also relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and sensor networks (cs.SI).
